desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the first tuple is ordered before or the same as the second in a lexicographical ordering.
declaration: func <= <A, B, C, D, E, F>(lhs: (A, B, C, D, E, F), rhs: (A, B, C, D, E, F)) -> Bool where A : Comparable, B : Comparable, C : Comparable, D : Comparable, E : Comparable, F : Comparable
